Native American |1%||0.2%||1.3%||1.0% |- ! Foreign |4%||22.4%||N/A||N/A |}  ===Residential life=== The campus has fourteen residence halls, the newest of which opened in Spring 2007. On-campus housing can hold more than 7,100 students.   Jester Center is the largest residence hall with its capacity of 2,945.   Academic enrollment exceeds the on-campus housing capacity; as a result, most students must live in private residence halls, housing cooperatives, apartments, or with Greek organizations and other off-campus residences. The Division of Housing and Food Service, which already has the largest market share of 7,000 of the estimated 27,000 beds in the campus area, plans to expand to 9,000 beds.
